column3: Godwin of the Wood Wailers has a report that requires urgent delivery.
Godwin has entrusted you with a classified report on recent happenings in the vicinity of Fallgourd Float. Deliver it to Vortefaurt of the Twin Adder with due haste.
Godwin's report relayed sightings of a masked man that have stirred alarm in Fallgourd Float. Might the menacing figure described be an Ascian?
Deliver the Fallgourd report to Vortefaurt.
Hail, adventurer. If you would not be averse to courier duty, I have a report that must be delivered to Florentel's Spire with all haste.
Mind you, this information is highly classified. I trust you to deliver it directly to the hands of Serpent Lieutenant Vortefaurt─<Emphasis>without</Emphasis> sneaking a peek for yourself.
These parts abound with particularly ferocious beasts. You'd do well to keep a wide berth, adventurer, lest I be left to clean your carcass off the forest floor.

A report from Godwin, you say? Very well, let us see... Traveling merchant waylaid by Qiqirn bandits, adventurer's hand bitten clean off by feral ziz, et cetera, et cetera... <sigh> The usual banalities.
Hm? What's this? Sightings of a masked man...? “No casualties yet reported, but due vigilance should be exercised.”
Troubling news, indeed─these parts are perilous enough without some masked marauder stirring up trouble. Thank you, friend. Rest assured that the Adder will be on the lookout for this interloper.
